{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882703515,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb8de3001a0VlgfEMnpRxBO","messageID":"msg_d7adb868b001r1Zp9q106rlda2","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_67f430d4e16a46ea95879249","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## HTTP Session Factory\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: create_session\n19: The system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: default pool parameters\n22: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called with no arguments\n23: - **WHEN** the session is created\n24: - **THEN** `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` SHALL be mounted for both `http://` and `https://` prefixes\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: custom pool parameters\n27: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n28: - **WHEN** the session is created\n29: - **THEN** both adapters SHALL use the provided pool parameters\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## ControlPlaneClient\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient constructor\n36: The system SHALL initialize `ControlPlaneClient` with URL resolution from arguments or environment, and auth token resolution from arguments or ServiceAccount file.\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: base URL from argument\n39: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")`\n40: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n41: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm:8080\"`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: base URL from environment\n44: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is `None` and env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n45: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n46: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: auth token from argument\n49: - **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n50: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n51: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: auth token from ServiceAccount file\n54: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` or empty and file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `\"sa-token\\n\"`\n55: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n56: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer sa-token\"`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: auth token file not found\n59: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and the ServiceAccount token file does not exist\n60: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n61: - **THEN** `read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"` and `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be set\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: empty token skips Authorization header\n64: - **GIVEN** resolved token is empty string\n65: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n66: - **THEN** `session.headers` SHALL NOT contain `Authorization`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: default Content-Type header\n69: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n70: - **WHEN** session headers are inspected\n71: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Content-Type\"]` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: default timeout parameters\n74: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called with no timeout arguments\n75: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n76: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.create_session\n79: The system SHALL POST to the Workload Manager to create a Code Interpreter session and return the session ID.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: successful session creation\n82: - **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"key\": \"val\"})`\n83: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n84: - **THEN** `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"val\"}}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: response contains sessionId\n87: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}}`\n88: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n89: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: response missing sessionId\n92: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {}}`\n93: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n94: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `ValueError`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: request timeout tuple\n97: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n98: - **WHEN** any request is sent\n99: - **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session\n102: The system SHALL DELETE a session and treat 404 as success.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: successful deletion\n105: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 200\n106: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n107: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: 404 treated as success\n110: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent\")` returns HTTP 404\n111: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n112: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: other error logged and returns False\n115: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 500\n116: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n117: - **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.close\n120: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: close releases session\n123: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.close()` is called\n124: - **WHEN** the method executes\n125: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructor\n132: The system SHALL initialize the data plane client with base URL derived from router URL or explicit `base_url`.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: base URL from router URL\n135: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")`\n136: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n137: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: base URL explicit override\n140: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom/url/\")`\n141: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n142: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://custom/url/\"` and router/namespace/cr_name SHALL be ignored for URL construction\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: session header set\n145: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n146: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n147: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be `\"sess-1\"`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: default timeouts\n150: - **GIVEN** no timeout arguments provided\n151: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n152: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: _request method\n155: The system SHALL send HTTP requests with appropriate headers based on whether a body is present.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: JSON body request\n158: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", body=b'{\"cmd\": \"ls\"}')`\n159: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n160: - **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set on the request and URL SHALL be `urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/execute\")`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: request without body\n163: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"GET\", \"api/files\")`\n164: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n165: - **THEN** no `Content-Type` override SHALL be set (session defaults apply)\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: execute_command\n168: The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout, adding a 2-second buffer to read timeout.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: command with explicit timeout\n171: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=10.0)`\n172: - **WHEN** the request is built\n173: - **THEN** HTTP read timeout SHALL be `12.0` (`timeout + 2.0`) and body SHALL contain `{\"command\": [\"sleep 10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: command with default timeout\n176: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=None)` and `self.timeout` is `120`\n177: - **WHEN** the request is built\n178: - **THEN** effective timeout SHALL be `120` and body SHALL contain `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: command string split into list\n181: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")`\n182: - **WHEN** the body is constructed\n183: - **THEN** `command` field SHALL be `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (split by whitespace)\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: non-zero exit code raises error\n186: - **GIVEN** response JSON is `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n187: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n188: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")` SHALL be raised\n189: \n190: ### Requirement: run_code\n191: The system SHALL write code to a timestamped file and execute it via the interpreter.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n194: - **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hi')\")`\n195: - **WHEN** the method executes\n196: - **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with a timestamped `.py` file, then `execute_command(\"python3 <file>\")`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: language alias normalization\n199: - **GIVEN** `language` is `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n200: - **WHEN** `run_code` executes\n201: - **THEN** it SHALL be treated as Python and follow the same path as `\"python\"`\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: write_file\n204: The system SHALL POST base64-encoded content to `api/files`.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: write file with base64 content\n207: - **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")`\n208: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n209: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'hello'>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n210: \n211: ### Requirement: upload_file\n212: The system SHALL POST multipart form data to `api/files` with session header.\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: multipart upload\n215: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")`\n216: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n217: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id` explicitly set\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: download_file\n220: The system SHALL GET file content with streaming and write to local path.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: streaming download\n223: - **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path.txt\", \"/local/out.txt\")`\n224: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n225: - **THEN** GET `api/files/remote/path.txt` (with `lstrip(\"/\")`), `stream=True`, and content SHALL be written in chunks to `/local/out.txt`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: clean path strips leading slash\n228: - **GIVEN** `remote_path = \"/absolute/path.txt\"`\n229: - **WHEN** download URL is constructed\n230: - **THEN** `clean_path` SHALL be `\"absolute/path.txt\"`\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: list_files\n233: The system SHALL GET file listing with path query parameter.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: list files in path\n236: - **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/some/path\")`\n237: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n238: - **THEN** GET `api/files?path=/some/path`\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close\n241: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: close releases session\n244: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n245: - **WHEN** the method executes\n246: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor\n253: The system SHALL initialize the agent runtime data plane client with invocation base URL.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: base URL construction\n256: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n257: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n258: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER class constant\n261: - **GIVEN** the class definition\n262: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER` is accessed\n263: - **THEN** the value SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: bootstrap_session_id\n266: The system SHALL GET the invocation base URL and extract session ID from response header.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: session ID extracted from header\n269: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` returns response with header `x-agentcube-session-id: \"new-session\"`\n270: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"new-session\"`\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: missing session ID header raises error\n274: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id`\n275: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n277: \n278: ### Requirement: invoke\n279: The system SHALL POST JSON payload to the invocation base URL with session header.\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: invoke with session header\n282: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s1\", payload={\"msg\": \"hello\"})`\n283: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n284: - **THEN** POST `{base_url}` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: s1` and `Content-Type: application/json`, body SHALL be JSON `{\"msg\": \"hello\"}`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: invoke with default timeout\n287: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=None)`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `self.timeout=120`\n288: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n289: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: invoke with custom timeout\n292: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=60.0)`\n293: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n294: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 60.0)`\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: invoke without session_id raises error\n297: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n298: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n299: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n302: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: close releases session\n305: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n306: - **WHEN** the method executes\n307: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Connection Pool Reuse\n312: \n313: ### Requirement: Session reuse within client\n314: The system SHALL reuse a single `requests.Session` instance per client for all HTTP operations.\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: same session for multiple requests\n317: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` calls `create_session` then `delete_session`\n318: - **WHEN** both requests are sent\n319: - **THEN** they SHALL use the same `self.session` instance\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: independent sessions across clients\n322: - **GIVEN** two `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instances are created\n323: - **WHEN** their session objects are compared\n324: - **THEN** `client1.session` and `client2.session` SHALL be different objects\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Utility Functions\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: read_token_from_file\n331: The system SHALL read and strip token content from a file, returning empty string on missing file.\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: file exists with trailing newline\n334: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/token` contains `\"my-token\\n\"`\n335: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"`\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: file not found\n339: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/nonexistent` does not exist\n340: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/nonexistent\")` is called\n341: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"\"`\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: get_logger\n344: The system SHALL create a named logger with configurable level.\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: logger with custom level\n347: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_module\", level=\"DEBUG\")`\n348: - **WHEN** the function executes\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Logger named `\"test_module\"` with level `DEBUG`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Exception Hierarchy\n354: \n355: ### Requirement: Exception classes\n356: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n359: - **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=\"ls\")`\n360: - **WHEN** the exception is created\n361: - **THEN** `exc.exit_code` SHALL be `1`, `exc.stderr` SHALL be `\"err\"`, `exc.command` SHALL be `\"ls\"`, and `str(exc)` SHALL contain `\"Command failed (exit 1): err\"`\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: exception inheritance\n364: - **GIVEN** the exception classes are defined\n365: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n366: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL all be subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Session Factory\n\n### Requirement: create_session\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882703504,"end":1775882703513}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882705164,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb9300001gZ3oOVaLL3ziRH","messageID":"msg_d7adb868b001r1Zp9q106rlda2","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0ee2174be7c94a9e9b99a637","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `integrations`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/integrations.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: <!-- TODO: Write the delta spec covering all requirements and scenarios -->\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Status\n17: \n18: - [ ] Spec review\n19: - [ ] Implementation\n20: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `integrations`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/integrations.md`\n\n## Scope\n\n<!-- TODO: Write the delta spec covering all requirements and scenarios -->\n\n---\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Spec review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882705145,"end":1775882705162}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775882705221,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb9933001mrq1HYcJQeyVOQ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7adb868b001r1Zp9q106rlda2","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":31139,"input":30964,"output":148,"reasoning":27,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.008834989}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882708660,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adba6b0001mbn0kg1DSZG3iT","messageID":"msg_d7adb9967001Hp8BW1LjldkCHi","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882711167,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adbabfc001Fru7vBrruecMLb","messageID":"msg_d7adb9967001Hp8BW1LjldkCHi","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6c9604bb4bbe4ae0a8fcac69","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035: client-go 类型客户端生成 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `client-go`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the generated Kubernetes client-go library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, module path `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`. It SHALL provide a typed Clientset, per-resource REST clients, SharedInformerFactory, Listers, and in-memory Fake clients for the `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. All code SHALL be generated via `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` using `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Clientset\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Interface contract\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide a `Clientset` implementing `Interface` with discovery and group accessor methods.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Interface exposes Discovery and RuntimeV1alpha1\n23: - **GIVEN** the `Interface` type is defined in `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n24: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface` and `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Clientset struct embeds DiscoveryClient\n28: - **GIVEN** the `Clientset` struct is defined\n29: - **WHEN** the struct fields are inspected\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and hold `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Clientset constructors\n33: \n34: The system SHALL provide four constructor functions for creating `Clientset` instances.\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: NewForConfig creates clientset from rest.Config\n37: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` pointing to a Kubernetes API server\n38: - **WHEN** `NewForConfig(c)` is called\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(*Clientset, nil)` with all group clients initialized, or `(*Clientset, error)` on failure\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: NewForConfigAndClient uses custom http.Client\n42: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` and `*http.Client`\n43: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient(c, httpClient)` is called\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` using the provided HTTP client for transport\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie panics on invalid config\n47: - **GIVEN** an invalid `*rest.Config` (e.g., malformed host)\n48: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL panic\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie succeeds with valid config\n52: - **GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`\n53: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie(c)` is called\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` without panicking\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: New creates clientset from rest.Interface\n57: - **GIVEN** a pre-configured `rest.Interface`\n58: - **WHEN** `New(restInterface)` is called\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `*Clientset` with the typed client wired to the provided interface\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1 group accessor\n62: \n63: The system SHALL provide access to the `runtime/v1alpha1` API group client.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1 returns typed group client\n66: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `cs.RuntimeV1alpha1()` is called\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Typed Client — runtime/v1alpha1\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n75: \n76: The system SHALL provide a group-level interface exposing REST client and resource getters.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface contract\n79: - **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` is defined in `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n80: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `RESTClient() rest.Interface`, `AgentRuntimesGetter`, and `CodeInterpretersGetter`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Client implements the interface\n84: - **GIVEN** the `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` struct\n85: - **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL implement all methods of `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: REST defaults are configured correctly\n89: - **GIVEN** a `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` instance\n90: - **WHEN** its REST client is inspected\n91: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` SHALL be `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion`, `APIPath` SHALL be `/apis`, and negotiated serializer SHALL come from `clientset/versioned/scheme`\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime typed client\n94: \n95: The system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `agentruntimes` resource.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimesGetter interface\n98: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimesGetter` interface\n99: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Create\n103: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a valid `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n104: - **WHEN** `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n105: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes` and return the created object\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Update\n108: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an existing `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n109: - **WHEN** `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the resource URL and return the updated object\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — UpdateStatus\n113: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and an `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` with modified status\n114: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, opts)` is called\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL PUT to the `/status` subresource endpoint\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Get\n118: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n119: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n120: - **THEN** it SHALL GET the resource and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — List\n123: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n124: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, opts)` is called\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL GET the collection and return `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Delete\n128: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` and a resource name\n129: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, name, opts)` is called\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL DELETE the resource and return `nil` on success or `error` on failure\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — DeleteCollection\n133: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n134: - **WHEN** `DeleteCollection(ctx, deleteOpts, listOpts)` is called\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL DELETE all resources matching `listOpts`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Watch\n138: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n139: - **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, opts)` is called\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL establish a watch stream and return `watch.Interface`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInterface CRUD — Patch\n143: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`, name, patch type, and patch data\n144: - **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, name, pt, data, opts, subresources...)` is called\n145: - **THEN** it SHALL PATCH the resource and return the patched `*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime`\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime resource plural\n148: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime REST client\n149: - **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n150: - **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter typed client\n153: \n154: The system SHALL provide a typed REST client for the `codeinterpreters` resource with the same method shape as AgentRuntime.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: CodeInterpretersGetter interface\n157: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpretersGetter` interface\n158: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInterface methods\n162: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInterface`\n163: - **WHEN** its methods are inspected\n164: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` with types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n167: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter REST client\n168: - **WHEN** the resource path is constructed\n169: - **THEN** the plural form SHALL be `codeinterpreters`\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Expansion hooks\n172: \n173: The system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for custom method injection.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeExpansion interface\n176: - **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n177: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeExpansion` is inspected\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterExpansion interface\n181: - **GIVEN** `generated_expansion.go`\n182: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterExpansion` is inspected\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty interface `interface{}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Scheme\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n190: \n191: The system SHALL register all `runtime/v1alpha1` types with a shared `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec`.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: register.go builds Scheme\n194: - **GIVEN** `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n195: - **WHEN** the package is loaded\n196: - **THEN** `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec` SHALL be initialized as package-level variables\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: AddToScheme registers v1alpha1 types\n199: - **GIVEN** `AddToScheme` is called on a `*runtime.Scheme`\n200: - **WHEN** registration completes\n201: - **THEN** all `runtime/v1alpha1` types (AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeList, CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterList) SHALL be registered\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Informer Factory\n206: \n207: ### Requirement: SharedInformerFactory interface\n208: \n209: The system SHALL provide a shared informer factory for cache-based event distribution.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: SharedInformerFactory contract\n212: - **GIVEN** the `SharedInformerFactory` interface in `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n213: - **WHEN** the interface is inspected\n214: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` and declare `Start`, `Shutdown`, `WaitForCacheSync`, `ForResource`, `InformerFor`, and `Runtime()` methods\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactory constructor\n217: - **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `defaultResync time.Duration`\n218: - **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactory(client, defaultResync)` is called\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `SharedInformerFactory` with the provided resync interval\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions\n222: - **GIVEN** a client, resync duration, and options (`WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`)\n223: - **WHEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options...)` is called\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL return a configured `SharedInformerFactory` applying all provided options\n225: \n226: ### Requirement: Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync lifecycle\n227: \n228: The system SHALL manage informer lifecycle through start, shutdown, and cache sync operations.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Start begins informer goroutines\n231: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with registered informers\n232: - **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n233: - **THEN** all registered informers SHALL begin watching their resources until `stopCh` is closed\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Shutdown stops all informers\n236: - **GIVEN** a running `SharedInformerFactory`\n237: - **WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called\n238: - **THEN** all informers SHALL be stopped and resources released\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync blocks until caches are ready\n241: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with started informers\n242: - **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL block until all informers have synced their caches or `stopCh` is closed, returning a `map[reflect.Type]bool`\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Group and version accessors\n246: \n247: The system SHALL provide hierarchical accessors for group → version → informer navigation.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Runtime() returns group interface\n250: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`\n251: - **WHEN** `factory.Runtime()` is called\n252: - **THEN** it SHALL return `externalversionsruntime.Interface`\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: V1alpha1() returns version interface\n255: - **GIVEN** a group `Interface`\n256: - **WHEN** `group.V1alpha1()` is called\n257: - **THEN** it SHALL return `v1alpha1.Interface` with `AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` accessors\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Per-type informers\n260: \n261: The system SHALL provide informer and lister access for each resource type.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeInformer interface\n264: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface\n265: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n266: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeInformer constructor\n269: - **GIVEN** a `versioned.Interface` client and `resync time.Duration`\n270: - **WHEN** `NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resync, indexers)` is called\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` watching AgentRuntime resources\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer\n274: - **GIVEN** a client, namespace, resync, indexers, and `tweakListOptions`\n275: - **WHEN** `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer` is called\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL return an informer with list options modified by `tweakListOptions`\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterInformer mirrors AgentRuntimeInformer\n279: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterInformer` interface\n280: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n281: - **THEN** it SHALL declare the same methods as `AgentRuntimeInformer` but returning `CodeInterpreterLister`\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Generic resource routing\n284: \n285: The system SHALL route GVR lookups to the correct typed informer.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: ForResource routes agentruntimes\n288: - **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))`\n289: - **WHEN** the method is called\n290: - **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: ForResource routes codeinterpreters\n293: - **GIVEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\"))`\n294: - **WHEN** the method is called\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL return `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` wrapped in a `GenericInformer`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: ForResource returns error for unknown resource\n298: - **GIVEN** `ForResource` with an unrecognized GVR\n299: - **WHEN** the method is called\n300: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(nil, error)`\n301: \n302: ### Requirement: internalinterfaces\n303: \n304: The system SHALL define base factory interfaces for informer construction.\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: NewInformerFunc signature\n307: - **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces` package\n308: - **WHEN** `NewInformerFunc` is inspected\n309: - **THEN** it SHALL be `func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n312: - **GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory` interface\n313: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})` and `InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: TweakListOptionsFunc\n317: - **GIVEN** the `TweakListOptionsFunc` type\n318: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n319: - **THEN** it SHALL be `func(*metav1.ListOptions)`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ## Listers\n324: \n325: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeLister\n326: \n327: The system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for AgentRuntime objects.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister interface\n330: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeLister` interface in `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n331: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n332: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister`, and `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface\n335: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` interface\n336: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n337: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, `Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)`, and `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: NewAgentRuntimeLister uses correct GroupResource\n340: - **GIVEN** `NewAgentRuntimeLister(indexer cache.Indexer)` is called\n341: - **WHEN** the lister is created\n342: - **THEN** it SHALL use `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()` for error reporting\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterLister\n345: \n346: The system SHALL provide a read-only caching layer for CodeInterpreter objects with the same pattern.\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister interface\n349: - **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterLister` interface\n350: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL declare `List`, `CodeInterpreters(namespace) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`, and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: NewCodeInterpreterLister uses correct GroupResource\n354: - **GIVEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister(indexer)` is called\n355: - **WHEN** the lister is created\n356: - **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`\n357: \n358: ### Requirement: Lister expansion interfaces\n359: \n360: The system SHALL provide empty expansion interfaces for all lister types.\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: All four expansion interfaces are empty\n363: - **GIVEN** `expansion_generated.go`\n364: - **WHEN** the file is inspected\n365: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion`, `AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion`, `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion`, and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion` SHALL all be empty interfaces\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## Fake Clients\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Fake typed clients\n372: \n373: The system SHALL provide in-memory fake implementations of typed interfaces for testing.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Fake runtime group client\n376: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n377: - **WHEN** the `FakeRuntimeV1alpha1` struct is inspected\n378: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` and embed `*testing.Fake`\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Fake AgentRuntime client\n381: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n382: - **WHEN** the fake AgentRuntime client is inspected\n383: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Fake CodeInterpreter client\n386: - **GIVEN** `fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n387: - **WHEN** the fake CodeInterpreter client is inspected\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterInterface` using `*testing.Fake` actions\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Fake clientset\n391: \n392: The system SHALL provide a fake `Clientset` for integration testing without a real API server.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: NewSimpleClientset creates fake clientset with objects\n395: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)` is called with initial runtime objects\n396: - **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n397: - **THEN** it SHALL contain the provided objects in its tracker and implement `versioned.Interface`\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: NewClientset creates fake clientset with custom reactor\n400: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewClientset(client, objects...)` is called\n401: - **WHEN** the fake clientset is returned\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `*restclient.RESTClient` and tracker\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Fake clientset Scheme registration\n405: - **GIVEN** `fake/register.go`\n406: - **WHEN** the package is loaded\n407: - **THEN** it SHALL wire the same scheme as the real clientset for type recognition\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ## Regeneration\n412: \n413: ### Requirement: make gen-client target\n414: \n415: The system SHALL provide a Makefile target to regenerate all client-go code.\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: make gen-client runs update-codegen.sh\n418: - **GIVEN** the Makefile defines `gen-client`\n419: - **WHEN** `make gen-client` is executed\n420: - **THEN** it SHALL invoke `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: update-codegen.sh uses correct code-generator version\n423: - **GIVEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n424: - **WHEN** the script is inspected\n425: - **THEN** it SHALL use `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: code-generator flags include --with-watch\n428: - **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation in `update-codegen.sh`\n429: - **WHEN** the command is inspected\n430: - **THEN** it SHALL include `--with-watch` flag for watch support\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: output package is correct\n433: - **GIVEN** the code-generator invocation\n434: - **WHEN** the output package flag is inspected\n435: - **THEN** it SHALL be `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## File Index\n440: \n441: ### Requirement: All generated files exist at expected paths\n442: \n443: The system SHALL produce the following file structure under `client-go/`.\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Clientset files\n446: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n447: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n448:   - `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n449:   - `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go`\n450:   - `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go`\n451:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go`\n452:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go`\n453:   - `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go`\n454: \n455: #### Scenario: Typed client files\n456: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n457: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n458:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n459:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n460:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n461:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go`\n462:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n463:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go`\n464:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go`\n465:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go`\n466:   - `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go`\n467: \n468: #### Scenario: Informer files\n469: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n470: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n471:   - `informers/externalversions/factory.go`\n472:   - `informers/externalversions/generic.go`\n473:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`\n474:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`\n475:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n476:   - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n477:   - `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`\n478: \n479: #### Scenario: Lister files\n480: - **GIVEN** code generation completes\n481: - **THEN** the following files SHALL exist:\n482:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n483:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n484:   - `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## File Changes\n489: \n490: | Action | File | Description |\n491: |--------|------|-------------|\n492: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n493: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n494: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n495: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n496: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n497: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n498: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n499: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n500: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n501: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n502: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n503: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n504: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n505: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n506: | Create | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n507: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, lifecycle |\n508: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n509: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n510: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n511: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n512: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n513: | Create | `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Base factory interface + types |\n514: | Create | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n515: | Create | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n516: | Create | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n\n(End of file - total 516 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-035: client-go 类型客户端生成 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `client-go`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/c