{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882831751,"sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","part":{"id":"prt_d7adbce6d001YRlIMKjPvW5quD","messageID":"msg_d7adbb5bf001MmgjA9DxXSk54K","sessionID":"ses_28524a0feffeG3ef3pZQgglh6j","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_c1163156432e4452b4cc3cb6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `integrations`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `integrations/design.md`, `integrations/spec.md`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the AgentCube Dify plugin integration — plugin bootstrap, manifest structure, provider descriptor, tool schema, credential validation, tool invocation, execution delegation to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`, and plugin dependency pins. It also covers the PCAP analyzer example application — FastAPI service, LangChain/LangGraph agent composition, sandbox orchestration via `SandboxRunner`, container image, and Kubernetes deployment.\n\n---\n\n## Dify Plugin Bootstrap\n\n### Requirement: Plugin process entrypoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose a `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin runs with timeout configuration\n- **GIVEN** `main.py` is executed by the Dify plugin runtime\n- **WHEN** the module loads\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` and block until the host stops it\n\n#### Scenario: MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT value\n- **GIVEN** the `DifyPluginEnv` is constructed\n- **WHEN** the timeout parameter is inspected\n- **THEN** `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` SHALL be `120` (seconds)\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Manifest\n\n### Requirement: Root manifest.yaml structure\n\nThe system SHALL ship a `manifest.yaml` at the plugin root declaring all required metadata fields for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n\n#### Scenario: Top-level identity fields\n- **GIVEN** `manifest.yaml` is parsed\n- **WHEN** the top-level keys are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `version: \"0.0.2\"`, `type: \"plugin\"`, `author: \"volcano-sh\"`, and `name: \"agentcube\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Multilingual label\n- **GIVEN** the `label` field in the manifest\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a map with keys `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, each mapping to `\"Agentcube\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Multilingual description\n- **GIVEN** the `description` field in the manifest\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a multilingual map containing localized strings for AgentCube description\n\n#### Scenario: Icon fields\n- **GIVEN** the manifest icon configuration\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** `icon` SHALL be `\"icon.png\"` and `icon_dark` SHALL be `\"icon-dark.png\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource permissions\n- **GIVEN** the `resource` field in the manifest\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `memory` and a `permission` subtree with flags and sizes for `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, and `storage`\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin tools registration\n- **GIVEN** the `plugins.tools` field\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a list containing `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n\n#### Scenario: Meta section\n- **GIVEN** the `meta` field in the manifest\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `version`, `arch` (list containing `amd64` and `arm64`), `runner` (map with `language: \"python\"`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: \"main\"`), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n\n#### Scenario: Additional metadata fields\n- **GIVEN** the manifest root\n- **WHEN** optional fields are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, and `verified`\n\n---\n\n## Provider Descriptor\n\n### Requirement: provider/agentcube.yaml structure\n\nThe system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the Agentcube provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python implementation.\n\n#### Scenario: Provider identity\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is parsed\n- **WHEN** the `identity` section is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual map), and `icon`\n\n#### Scenario: Tools list\n- **GIVEN** the `tools` field in the provider descriptor\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Python source pointer\n- **GIVEN** the `extra.python.source` field\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `\"provider/agentcube.py\"`\n\n#### Scenario: OAuth schema is commented out\n- **GIVEN** the provider descriptor file content\n- **WHEN** the file is read as text\n- **THEN** any `oauth_schema` block SHALL be present only as comments (not active YAML)\n\n---\n\n## Tool Parameter Schema\n\n### Requirement: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml schema\n\nThe system SHALL declare a tool schema with connection endpoints, language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n\n#### Scenario: Tool identity\n- **GIVEN** the tool YAML `identity` section\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** `identity.name` SHALL be `\"agentcube-code-interpreter\"`, `identity.author` SHALL be `\"agentcube\"`, and `label`/`description` SHALL include both `human` and `llm` string variants\n\n#### Scenario: Required string parameters\n- **GIVEN** the `parameters` list\n- **WHEN** parameters with `required: true` are filtered\n- **THEN** they SHALL include `router_url` (type: string, form: form) and `workload_manager_url` (type: string, form: form)\n\n#### Scenario: Optional language select\n- **GIVEN** the `language` parameter\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `type: select`, `required: false`, `form: llm`, and `options` SHALL be `[\"python\", \"javascript\", \"typescript\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Optional code and command parameters\n- **GIVEN** the `parameters` list\n- **WHEN** optional parameters are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `code` (type: string), `command` (type: string), `session_id` (type: string), `session_reuse` (type: boolean), and `code_interpreter_id` (type: string), all with `required: false` and `form: llm`\n\n#### Scenario: Parameter documentation\n- **GIVEN** each parameter entry\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form`\n\n#### Scenario: Python source pointer\n- **GIVEN** the tool YAML `extra.python.source` field\n- **WHEN** it is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `\"tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\"`\n\n---\n\n## Provider Implementation\n\n### Requirement: AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider class\n\nThe system SHALL implement a Dify `ToolProvider` subclass with credential validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Class inheritance\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.py`\n- **WHEN** the class definition is inspected\n- **THEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` SHALL inherit from `dify_plugin.ToolProvider`\n\n#### Scenario: Import of validation error\n- **GIVEN** the imports in `provider/agentcube.py`\n- **WHEN** the file is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL import `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` from `dify_plugin.errors.tool`\n\n#### Scenario: _validate_credentials method signature\n- **GIVEN** the provider class\n- **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL accept `self` and `credentials: dict[str, Any]` and return `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Validation error propagation\n- **GIVEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition\n- **WHEN** an exception is caught\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))` with the exception message\n\n#### Scenario: Successful validation returns quietly\n- **GIVEN** credentials that pass validation\n- **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `None` without raising\n\n---\n\n## Tool Implementation\n\n### Requirement: AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool class\n\nThe system SHALL implement a Dify `Tool` subclass that delegates execution to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Class inheritance and imports\n- **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n- **WHEN** the file is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL import `Tool` from `dify_plugin`, `ToolInvokeMessage` from `dify_plugin.entities.tool`, and `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: _invoke delegates to execute\n- **GIVEN** `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any])` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `self.execute(**tool_parameters)` and yield `self.create_json_message(result)`\n\n#### Scenario: _invoke returns a generator\n- **GIVEN** the `_invoke` method signature\n- **WHEN** the return type is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`\n\n### Requirement: execute method signature\n\nThe system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters matching the tool schema, delegating to the AgentCube SDK.\n\n#### Scenario: execute parameter defaults\n- **GIVEN** the `execute` method signature\n- **WHEN** default values are inspected\n- **THEN** `language` SHALL default to `\"python\"` and `session_reuse` SHALL default to `False`\n\n#### Scenario: execute accepts all tool parameters\n- **GIVEN** the `execute` method\n- **WHEN** its parameters are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL accept `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language`, `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and `**kwargs`\n\n#### Scenario: execute delegates to CodeInterpreterClient\n- **GIVEN** valid `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `execute` is called with `code` or `command`\n- **THEN** it SHALL instantiate or use `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube` to perform the corresponding remote operation\n\n#### Scenario: execute returns JSON-serializable result\n- **GIVEN** `execute` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the return value is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a JSON-serializable object suitable for `create_json_message`\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Dependencies\n\n### Requirement: requirements.txt pins\n\nThe system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n\n#### Scenario: dify-plugin version bounds\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are parsed\n- **THEN** `dify-plugin` SHALL satisfy `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n\n#### Scenario: agentcube-sdk version lower bound\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are parsed\n- **THEN** `agentcube-sdk` SHALL satisfy `>=0.0.10`\n\n---\n\n## PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Service\n\n### Requirement: Application startup and configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup.\n\n#### Scenario: API key required at startup\n- **GIVEN** the environment lacks `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent)\n- **WHEN** `on_startup()` runs\n- **THEN** the application SHALL fail startup rather than serve requests without credentials\n\n#### Scenario: API base URL default\n- **GIVEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE` is not set\n- **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n- **THEN** `API_BASE_URL` SHALL default to `\"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Model name default\n- **GIVEN** `OPENAI_MODEL` is not set\n- **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n- **THEN** `MODEL_NAME` SHALL default to `\"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Code interpreter name default\n- **GIVEN** `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` is not set\n- **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n- **THEN** it SHALL default to `\"my-interpreter\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox namespace default\n- **GIVEN** `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` is not set\n- **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n- **THEN** it SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox warmup default\n- **GIVEN** `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` is not set\n- **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n- **THEN** it SHALL default to `5`\n\n#### Scenario: Server binding\n- **GIVEN** the application constants\n- **WHEN** server configuration is inspected\n- **THEN** `SERVER_HOST` SHALL be `\"0.0.0.0\"`, `SERVER_PORT` SHALL be `8000`, and `SERVER_RELOAD` SHALL be `True`\n\n### Requirement: Agent composition\n\nThe system SHALL compose LangChain/LangGraph agents for planning, execution, and reporting.\n\n#### Scenario: ReAct agent builder\n- **GIVEN** an LLM instance and system prompt\n- **WHEN** `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a ReAct agent using `langgraph.prebuilt.create_react_agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Planner agent builder\n- **GIVEN** an LLM instance\n- **WHEN** `build_planner_agent(llm)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an agent configured for script planning\n\n#### Scenario: Reporter agent builder\n- **GIVEN** an LLM instance\n- **WHEN** `build_reporter_agent(llm)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an agent configured for report generation\n\n#### Scenario: ReAct agent invocation\n- **GIVEN** a built ReAct agent and user text\n- **WHEN** `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the agent's response as a string\n\n### Requirement: Analysis orchestration\n\nThe system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis through planning, execution with retries, and reporting.\n\n#### Scenario: Plan script generation\n- **GIVEN** a planner agent and a local PCAP path\n- **WHEN** `_plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a script string generated by the planner agent\n\n#### Scenario: Script repair\n- **GIVEN** a reporter agent, a previous script, and execution results\n- **WHEN** `_repair_script(agent, prev_script, results)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a revised script string\n\n#### Scenario: Single execution in sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner`, local PCAP path, and script\n- **WHEN** `_execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the PCAP to the sandbox, execute the script, and return a list of result dicts\n\n#### Scenario: Analysis with retries\n- **GIVEN** analysis parameters and `max_retries=2`\n- **WHEN** `_analyze_with_retries(...)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL attempt planning, execution, and repair up to `max_retries` times, returning aggregated results\n\n#### Scenario: Report generation\n- **GIVEN** a reporter agent and execution results\n- **WHEN** `_report(agent, results)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a report string\n\n### Requirement: Analyze endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose `POST /analyze` accepting PCAP file uploads or paths.\n\n#### Scenario: Endpoint accepts file upload\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** `POST /analyze` is called with `pcap_file` as `UploadFile`\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL process the file and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n\n#### Scenario: Endpoint accepts file path\n- **GIVEN** a running service\n- **WHEN** `POST /analyze` is called with `pcap_path` as form field\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL process the file at the given path and return `AnalyzeResponse`\n\n#### Scenario: Response model structure\n- **GIVEN** `AnalyzeResponse` is defined\n- **WHEN** the model fields are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `script: str`, `results: List[Dict[str, Any]]`, and `report: str`\n\n#### Scenario: Endpoint signature\n- **GIVEN** the endpoint definition\n- **WHEN** the function signature is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` with `response_model=AnalyzeResponse`\n\n---\n\n## SandboxRunner\n\n### Requirement: SandboxRunner constructor\n\nThe system SHALL construct a `SandboxRunner` with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration.\n\n#### Scenario: Default constructor parameters\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `name` SHALL be `\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace` SHALL be `\"default\"`, and `warmup_sec` SHALL be `5`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom constructor parameters\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner(name=\"custom\", namespace=\"prod\", warmup_sec=10)`\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the instance fields SHALL reflect the provided values\n\n### Requirement: SandboxRunner file operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide `upload_file` and `upload_bytes` for staging artifacts in the sandbox.\n\n#### Scenario: upload_file stages local file\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance and local/remote paths\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the file from `local_path` to `remote_path` in the sandbox and return `True` on success\n\n#### Scenario: upload_bytes stages byte content\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance, byte data, and remote path\n- **WHEN** `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the bytes to `remote_path` in the sandbox and return `True` on success\n\n### Requirement: SandboxRunner command execution\n\nThe system SHALL execute commands in the remote sandbox context.\n\n#### Scenario: run executes command\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` and a shell command string\n- **WHEN** `run(command)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the command in the sandbox and return a `Dict[str, Any]` with structured results\n\n### Requirement: SandboxRunner lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL provide `stop` for cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: stop releases resources\n- **GIVEN** a running `SandboxRunner`\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL release sandbox resources and perform cleanup\n\n---\n\n## PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile structure\n\nThe system SHALL build a container image that installs dependencies with `uv`, vendors the `agentcube` SDK, and starts the FastAPI app.\n\n#### Scenario: Base image\n- **GIVEN** the `Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** the `FROM` instruction is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency installation\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build steps\n- **WHEN** the installation commands are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `uv venv` and `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube SDK vendoring\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile copy instructions\n- **WHEN** the file copies are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`\n\n#### Scenario: Application copy\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile copy instructions\n- **WHEN** the application copy is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to `./`\n\n#### Scenario: PYTHONPATH and port\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile environment and exposure\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** `PYTHONPATH` SHALL be `\"/app\"` and `EXPOSE 8000` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Default command\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile `CMD` instruction\n- **WHEN** it is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `[\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n## PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n\n### Requirement: Deployment manifest structure\n\nThe system SHALL supply a K8s `Deployment` manifest for the analyzer.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment metadata\n- **GIVEN** `deployment.yaml` is parsed\n- **WHEN** the Deployment metadata is inspected\n- **THEN** the name SHALL be `\"pcap-analyzer\"` and namespace SHALL be `\"default\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Container image and pull policy\n- **GIVEN** the container spec\n- **WHEN** image configuration is inspected\n- **THEN** `image` SHALL be `\"pcap-analyzer:latest\"` and `imagePullPolicy` SHALL be `\"IfNotPresent\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Container port\n- **GIVEN** the container ports\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** port `8000` TCP SHALL be exposed\n\n#### Scenario: Resource requests\n- **GIVEN** the container resources\n- **WHEN** requests are inspected\n- **THEN** `cpu` SHALL be `\"200m\"` and `memory` SHALL be `\"100Mi\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource limits\n- **GIVEN** the container resources\n- **WHEN** limits are inspected\n- **THEN** `cpu` SHALL be `\"1\"` and `memory` SHALL be `\"1Gi\"`\n\n#### Scenario: OPENAI_API_KEY from Secret\n- **GIVEN** the container environment variables\n- **WHEN** `OPENAI_API_KEY` env is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL reference Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` with key `openai-api-key`\n\n#### Scenario: Plain environment variables\n- **GIVEN** the container environment variables\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` SHALL be set as plain env values\n\n#### Scenario: Container command\n- **GIVEN** the container command/args\n- **WHEN** they are inspected\n- **THEN** `command` SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` and `args` SHALL be `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n## PCAP Analyzer Python Dependencies\n\n### Requirement: example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt\n\nThe system SHALL pin specific versions for the FastAPI, LangChain/LangGraph, and related dependencies.\n\n#### Scenario: FastAPI and uvicorn pins\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** the file is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0` and `uvicorn==0.38.0`\n\n#### Scenario: LangChain stack pins\n- **GIVEN** the requirements file\n- **WHEN** LangChain packages are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, and `langsmith==0.4.38`\n\n#### Scenario: Additional dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the requirements file\n- **WHEN** remaining packages are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `paramiko==4.0.0` and `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n\n#### Scenario: agentcube not in requirements\n- **GIVEN** the requirements file content\n- **WHEN** the file is searched for `agentcube`\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT be listed (the Dockerfile vendors it from the monorepo)\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Plugin entrypoint: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest with metadata, resources, meta, tools |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider descriptor with identity, tools, python source |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` with `_validate_credentials` |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema (router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session) |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with `_invoke` and `execute` |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` + `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` | Plugin usage guide |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` | Plugin documentation |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` | Privacy policy |\n| Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` | Dify ignore patterns |\n| Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app with agents, SandboxRunner, /analyze endpoint |\n| Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Pinned FastAPI, LangChain, LangGraph, paramiko, python-multipart |\n| Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | uv-based image with vendored agentcube SDK |\n| Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment with secrets, env, resources |\n| Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | PCAP analyzer documentation |\n\n---\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Spec review\n- [ ] Implementation\n- [ ] Verification\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882831731,"end":1775882831748}}}}
